Return a JSON object with schemaVersion, missionSummary, intentType, coverageStatus, startUrl (use current URL from browser state), allowlistedHosts, requiresClarification, clarificationQuestion, steps, verificationGoals, expectedEvidence, blockersToDetect, manualHandoffReasons, safetyNotes, confidence.

Each step must include id, action, label, target, selector, value, expectation, fieldMap, riskLevel, requiresApproval, evidenceLabel, stopOnFailure where relevant.
Allowed actions: navigate, wait_state, read_state, read_dom, query_interactive, click, type, select, extract_text, detect_blockers, verify_outcome, capture_evidence, stop_manual_handoff.
Do NOT include open_session — the session is already open.
Selectors may use testId, role/name, label, text, css, exact, or tagName.
Verification expectations may use text_visible, field_value, checkbox_checked, or url_includes.
Always end with capture_evidence to record the final page state as proof.
Never include raw HTML. Never include credentials, tokens, payment details, stealth, bypass, spoofing, or anti-bot evasion.
